<p>
    A high-fidelity mockup is an <em>almost</em>-functional HTML and CSS preview of the interfaces in your
    website.  You will need to write very little PHP code for this assignment, and I recommend that you
    focus your efforts on designing the intrfaces the way you would like them to look.
</p>

<p>
    In a high-fidelity mockup, the buttons, form fields, and other interactive UI components need to be present,
    but do not yet need to work or do anything.  This is a way of showing what your application will look like
    and giving a rough preview of functionality, not actually coding the project.
</p>

<p>
    Your submission must include UI mockups for each interface/page in your site.  You must also include an <em>index.php</em>
    file that lists each interface mockup page and provides a link to it.
</p>

