<h4>Technical Requirements</h4>

<p>
    Although you can (and should) create your high-fidelity mockups without the use
    of any PHP code, I must artificially require you to add some code to your submission.  This is
    so that I can evaluate your understanding of concepts we've covered during lecture.
</p>

<p>
    Therefore, you are required to make use of the following items somewhere in your mockup:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>A loop - Use a <em>for</em>, <em>foreach</em>, <em>while</em>, or <em>do&hellip;while</em> loop</li>
    <li>A multidimensional array - At least two dimensions of data are required</li>
    <li>A function - At least one custom function that you write.  Use as many built-in functions as you like</li>
</ul>

<p>
    It does not matter how you choose to implement the function, loop, and array, or even if the
    implementation makes much sense technically.  They must be present, and they must contribute to the
    output of the page in a meaningful way.
</p>

<p>
    One example of way to achieve this is to find an item in your mockups that consitute a list.  Create
    an array to hold the list items, and create a function with a loop in it to output the list.
</p>